race.comment: ROUND TWO (9) does plenty wrong but there's no denying he has talent. His on the quick back-up, having hit the line well from near-last over 1000m last Saturday. The rise to 1250m looks suitable and he's never missed a place over this track and distance. He can settle closer and prove hard to beat. MURPH (4) is a last-start winner that is racing well. There's no reason why he can't be in the finish again. Border hopper WELCOMETOTHESHOW (2) stormed home last start to finish just 0.4 away in third over 1200m at Ballarat. Looks a nice option for wider plays. STEEL TSUNAMI (10) hasn't made his mark in two runs since a spell, the latest when beaten 2.25 lengths into sixth over 1100m at Murray Bridge. Comes into play here.
